        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:50PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 849 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Callahan, or 25 miles south of Yreka, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Etna and Callahan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
